The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, March 2: Tata Steels European arm Corus has sold Cindu Chemicals to Koppers International, a global producer of carbon compounds with its headquarters in Pittsburgh, for an undisclosed amount. The Netherlands-based Cindu Chemicals was jointly held by Corus and Cindu BV.                             
	 New Delhi, March 2: State-owned companies are set to raise over Rs 56,000-crore debt by issuing corporate bonds and debentures during 2010-11. The government will use the proceeds to finance its fiscal deficit.                            
	 New Delhi, March 2: TCS has bagged a multi-year deal from the British government to administer the National Employment Savings Trust. The Personal Accounts Delivery Authority will sign a contract with TCS later this month, which will be divided into two stages for 10 years.                            
	 London, March 2: HSBCs India operations reported a 44 per cent decline in net profit at $374 million in 2009, because of growth in loan impairment charges and a deterioration in credit quality.                             
	 Mumbai, March 2: Jagdish Capoor, the non-executive chairman of BSEs board of directors, has submitted his resignation on health grounds.                                                                                                                          
